# Conduit test framework — project conventions

## What this project is

A Playwright + TypeScript test framework targeting the Conduit RealWorld API and UI at `https://conduit.bondaracademy.com`. The codebase is split into an API layer (with a custom `RequestHandler`, fixtures, logger, schema validation, custom matchers) and a UI layer (Playwright browser tests, Page Object Model).

## Naming conventions

| What | Convention | Examples |
|---|---|---|
| **Files and folders** | kebab-case | `article-crud.spec.ts`, `page-manager.ts`, `create-token.ts`, `request-objects/` |
| **Classes and types** | PascalCase | `class ArticlePage {}`, `type UserRole = ...` |
| **Functions, variables, methods** | camelCase | `async function createToken()`, `const authToken = ...` |
| **Test IDs / selectors** | kebab-case | `data-testid="submit-button"` |
| **JSON schema files** | `METHOD_resource_schema.json` | `GET_article_schema.json`, `POST_user_negative_schema.json` |
| **JSON request object files** | `METHOD_resource.json` | `POST_article.json`, `POST_user.json` |

## Project structure

```
config/
  test-config.ts              — central config: URLs + credentials
docs/
  api-endpoints.md            — centralized API endpoint list (used in tests + link to full spec)
request-objects/
  POST_article.json           — base payload for article creation
  POST_user.json              — base payload for user registration
response-schemas/
  articles/                   — Ajv JSON schemas for article responses
  users/                      — Ajv JSON schemas for user responses
page-objects/
  helper-base.ts              — base class: page property + shared helpers
  page-manager.ts             — facade: new PageManager(page) → navigateTo(), auth(), article()
  navigation-page.ts          — extends HelperBase: navigation actions
  auth-page.ts                — extends HelperBase: login
  article-page.ts             — extends HelperBase: article create/update/delete/validation
tests/api-tests/
  utils/
    request-handler.ts        — fluent HTTP client (THE API layer core)
    fixtures.ts               — Playwright fixtures: api, config, authToken, attachApiLogs
    logger.ts                 — APILogger: captures request/response per test
    custom-expect.ts          — custom matchers: shouldBe, shouldEqual, shouldMatchSchema
    schema-validator.ts       — Ajv validator + genson-js schema generator
    data-generator.ts         — Faker-powered generators: getNewRandomArticle, getNewRandomUser
  helpers/
    create-token.ts           — standalone login helper → "Token <jwt>"
  article-crud.spec.ts                  — article CRUD operations
  user-registration-negative.spec.ts    — registration negative cases (invalid username → 422)
tests/ui-tests/
  utils/
    ui-expect.ts              — UI assertion helpers
  article-form-validation.spec.ts       — article form validation (required fields)
  article-crud-flow.spec.ts             — full article CRUD via UI
  article-update-with-api-setup.spec.ts — article update via UI (article created via API)
playwright.config.ts          — projects: api-testing, api-testing-smoke, ui-testing
```

## Hard rules — never break these

- **Never bypass `RequestHandler`.** All API calls go through it. Do not use `request.get/post/...` directly in specs or fixtures.
- **Never import `test` from `@playwright/test` in API spec files.** Always import from `./utils/fixtures` to get the custom `api`, `config`, and `authToken` fixtures.
- **Never import `expect` from `@playwright/test` in API spec files.** Always import from `./utils/custom-expect` to get API-log-enriched matchers.
- **Never hardcode credentials or base URLs** in spec files. Use `config/test-config.ts`.
- **Never mutate imported request objects directly.** Always use `structuredClone` or `getNewRandomArticle()` / `getNewRandomUser()` from `data-generator.ts`.

## Adding new files

| What | Where |
|---|---|
| New API spec | `tests/api-tests/` |
| New UI spec | `tests/ui-tests/` |
| New page object | `page-objects/` |
| New request payload | `request-objects/` |
| New response schema | `response-schemas/<resource>/` |
| New data generator | `tests/api-tests/utils/data-generator.ts` |
| New custom matcher | `tests/api-tests/utils/custom-expect.ts` |

## Config and environments

Credentials and URLs live in `config/test-config.ts`. The `config` fixture injects them into any API test — no direct imports needed in API specs. UI specs import `config` directly from `config/test-config.ts`.
